    "created_at": "2016-03-22T08:30:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-03-22T08:34:53Z",
    "body": "After whole morning of trying and testing. I kinda found a solution. \nI set the \"x\" and \"y\" value (window positioning) of the browser window option to be in the second screen. So, every time my app will open full screen in my second screen. Take note that value x is positive for the second screen on the right side while x is negative for the second screen on the left side.\nIs this the best way guys? Any other better ways? \n"
  },
